HEADWORD: Nom
<hw>Nom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Noun</er>.]</ety> <def>Name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Nom de guerre</b></col> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <cd>literally,
war name; hence, a fictitious name, or one assumed for a time.</cd> --
<col><b>Nom de plume</b></col> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <cd>literally, pen name;
hence, a name assumed by an author as his or her
signature.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noma</ent>⟦br⟧
